-- Peru Stocks: Banco Continental, Minsur, Southern Copper Advance
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2011-12-26T18:08:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-26/peru-stocks-banco-continental-minsur-southern-copper-advance.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:02 p.m. in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose for a third session, gaining
0.1 percent to 19,445.05. The  MSCI All Peru Capped Index  was
little changed at 2,525.37.  Copper and tin miners gained as both metals prices advanced
in  London , said Edwin Paz, a Lima-based trader with Provalor
SAB.  Southern Copper Corp.  (SCCO PE), Peru’s biggest copper
producer, rose for a third day, adding 2.1 percent to $31.50.
 Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, climbed 1.1 percent to 2.63 soles after it was given a
“buy” recommendation in new coverage by Celfin Capital
analysts including Isabel Darrigrandi.  Banco Continental SA  (CONTINC1 PE), the local unit of
 Spain ’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA, gained 1.8 percent
to 5.55 soles after Peru’s banking association said corporate
loans rose in November.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
